Document: VisualShaderNodeVectorFunc
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodevectorfunc.rst
Summary: A VisualShader node that performs vector functions.

Inherits: VisualShaderNode < Resource < RefCounted < Object

This node selects a vector function to execute. It can perform operations like dot product, cross product, distance, and normalization on input vectors.

Properties:
function (enum): The function to execute. Options are:
    FUNC_DOT_PRODUCT (0): Computes the dot product of two vectors.
    FUNC_CROSS_PRODUCT (1): Computes the cross product of two vectors.
    FUNC_DISTANCE (2): Computes the distance between two vectors.
    FUNC_NORMALIZE (3): Normalizes a vector to unit length.
    FUNC_LENGTH (4): Computes the length (magnitude) of a vector.
    FUNC_MIN (5): Computes the element-wise minimum of two vectors.
    FUNC_MAX (6): Computes the element-wise maximum of two vectors.
    FUNC_CLAMP (7): Clamps a vector's components within a range.
    FUNC_SQUARED_LENGTH (8): Computes the squared length (magnitude) of a vector.
    FUNC_REFLECT (9): Reflects a vector off a surface normal.
    FUNC_REFRACT (10): Refracts a vector through a surface.
    FUNC_ নেওয়া (11): Computes the component-wise absolute value of a vector.
    FUNC_CEIL (12): Computes the component-wise ceiling of a vector.
    FUNC_FLOOR (13): Computes the component-wise floor of a vector.
    FUNC_ROUND (14): Computes the component-wise rounding of a vector.
    FUNC_SIN (15): Computes the component-wise sine of a vector.
    FUNC_COS (16): Computes the component-wise cosine of a vector.
    FUNC_TAN (17): Computes the component-wise tangent of a vector.
    FUNC_ASIN (18): Computes the component-wise arcsine of a vector.
    FUNC_ACOS (19): Computes the component-wise arccosine of a vector.
    FUNC_ATAN (20): Computes the component-wise arctangent of a vector.
    FUNC_ATAN2 (21): Computes the component-wise arctangent of two vectors.
    FUNC_POW (22): Computes the component-wise power of two vectors.
    FUNC_EXP (23): Computes the component-wise exponential of a vector.
    FUNC_LOG (24): Computes the component-wise natural logarithm of a vector.
    FUNC_SQRT (25): Computes the component-wise square root of a vector.
    FUNC_ABS (26): Computes the component-wise absolute value of a vector.
    FUNC_SIGN (27): Computes the component-wise sign of a vector.
    FUNC_RADIANS (28): Converts degrees to radians.
    FUNC_DEGREES (29): Converts radians to degrees.
    FUNC_EXP2 (30): Computes the component-wise base-2 exponential of a vector.
    FUNC_LOG2 (31): Computes the component-wise base-2 logarithm of a vector.
    FUNC_HERMITE (32): Computes the Hermite interpolation between two vectors.
    FUNC_HERMITE_INVERSE (33): Computes the inverse Hermite interpolation between two vectors.
    FUNC_NORMALIZE_SAFE (34): Normalizes a vector to unit length, avoiding division by zero.
    FUNC_SMOOTHSTEP (35): Smoothly interpolates between two values.
    FUNC_STEP (36): Performs a step function.
    FUNC_MAX_RESERVED (37): Maximum reserved function index.

Input Ports:
a (Vector): The first input vector. Used for most functions.
b (Vector): The second input vector. Used for functions like dot product, cross product, distance, min, max, clamp, reflect, refract, atan2, pow, hermite, and smoothstep.
normal (Vector): The normal vector. Used for reflect and refract functions.
min (float): The minimum value for clamp and smoothstep functions.
max (float): The maximum value for clamp and smoothstep functions.
edge1 (float): The first edge for smoothstep and step functions.
edge2 (float): The second edge for smoothstep and step functions.

Output Ports:
default (Vector): The result of the vector function.
